race.comment: Another wide-open affair. MAKDANE (3) is flying and sets up well here. His past two starts since a Caulfield win have been good, only beaten by the highly progressive Zambardo last start who would surely be favourite here. Drawn barrier one again, he lands on speed, likes soft ground and will take plenty of getting past. PARTY CRASHER (10) is only second up from 1400m but will be fitter for that and showed plenty of ability as a 3yo. Would've loved one more run for him but he's worth keeping an eye on. QUELLO DORATO (19) is lightly raced and can measure up. BRAVE MISS (7) comes into this tougher assignment as a last start winner over 2025m at Cranbourne. In the mix.
